properties.areaDesc: Los Angeles County San Fernando Valley
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 26 at 12:28PM PST until January 27 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Areas of north to northeast winds 20 to 30 mph with
gusts to 40 mph.

* WHERE...San Fernando Valley.

* WHEN...From 9 PM this evening to noon PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for drivers of high profile
vehicles. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power
outages may result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Gusty winds will affect travel on
Interstate 5 and portions of the 101, 118, 170, 210, and 405
freeways.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects such as lawn furniture.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO NOON PST MONDAY
